abstract: Companies continue to press for higher premiums, saying they need protection against any sudden uptick in demand once people have more money to spend on their health.
snippet: Companies continue to press for higher premiums, saying they need protection against any sudden uptick in demand once people have more money to spend on their health.
lead_paragraph: The nation’s major health insurers are barreling into a third year of record profits, enriched in recent months by a lingering recessionary mind-set among Americans who are postponing or forgoing medical care.

headline.main: Health Insurers Making Record Profits as Many Postpone Care
headline.print_headline: Health Insurers Profit as Many Postpone Care
